# Motley Crews Agent Battle — overview

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `motley_crews_env/` | Rules engine: `legal_actions`, `step`, setup, win detection. Implements [rules/rules_spec.yaml](rules/rules_spec.yaml). |
| `motley_crews_play/` | Play layer: CLI (`__main__.py`), headless `match.py` + policies, Pygame UI (`pygame_app.py`). Sprites under `motley_crews_play/assets/sprites/`. |
| `rules/` | Game spec (`rules_spec.yaml`) and OCR reference text — not Python imports. |

Core types and state live in `motley_crews_env/types.py` and `motley_crews_env/state.py`; transitions and legality in `motley_crews_env/engine.py`.

## Run / install

From repo root (ensure repo root is on `PYTHONPATH` — the play package adds it when needed):

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt          # engine + pytest
pytest                                   # tests under tests/
```

Headless matches (no GUI):

```bash
python -m motley_crews_play --mode cpu-cpu --seed 0
python -m motley_crews_play --mode random-random --verbose
```

Pygame UI:

```bash
pip install -r requirements-play.txt
python -m motley_crews_play --ui
```

Use **Python 3.11 or 3.12** for pygame wheels on macOS; see comments in `requirements-play.txt` if SDL build fails.

